  {
    
    "name": "Section 5",
    "tag": "section",
    "class": "gps-601074040370627147 gps gpsil",
    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/j0rgbv-09/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=601062966636315570&sectionId=601074040370627147)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"ggpKPGr2lY9_text","label":"ggpKPGr2lY9_text","default":"<p><i>Here are the 7 reasons I'll never use anything else:</i></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg_OMjFb7h-_text","label":"gg_OMjFb7h-_text","default":"<p>REASON #1</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggyfoIFmSss_text","label":"ggyfoIFmSss_text","default":"My neck finally looks like it belongs to the rest of me again."},{"type":"html","id":"ggrVRNgz_yI_text","label":"ggrVRNgz_yI_text","default":"<p>I'm 57. And for the past few years, my neck has been my biggest insecurity.</p><p><br>The sagging. The loose skin under my chin. That \"turkey neck\" look that made me dread seeing photos of myself from the side. I felt like my face looked okay, but my neck was screaming \"OLD MAN\" to everyone who saw me.</p><p><br>I tried turtlenecks. I tried angling my chin up in photos. I even started growing a beard to hide it.</p><p><br>After 8 weeks with Omnis, my wife asked if I'd \"gotten something done.\" I hadn't—but my neck was visibly tighter. More defined. The sagging had reduced enough that I actually looked like me again. Not a younger me, exactly. Just... the me I still feel like on the inside.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggwXsCHHBXj_text","label":"ggwXsCHHBXj_text","default":"<p>REASON #2</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggldpxBFAXT_text","label":"ggldpxBFAXT_text","default":"It actually works while I sleep—no complicated routine required."},{"type":"html","id":"gg4n9VHkD1G_text","label":"gg4n9VHkD1G_text","default":"<p>I'm not a \"skincare routine\" guy. Never have been. Never will be.</p><p><br>Those systems with 4-5 different bottles? The ones that want you to cleanse, then tone, then serum, then moisturize, then eye cream, then SPF in the morning? Forget it. I tried one of those subscription boxes for three months and half the bottles sat unopened.</p><p><br>Omnis is one step. One cream. At night. Takes 30 seconds after I brush my teeth.</p><p><br>That's it. No morning routine. No remembering which bottle comes first. No feeling like I'm performing some elaborate ritual designed for someone with way more bathroom patience than me.</p><p><br>Apply it, go to sleep, wake up with better skin. That's a routine I can actually stick to.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggChkvV9L4v_text","label":"ggChkvV9L4v_text","default":"<p>REASON #3</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggq1wlxoeIa_text","label":"ggq1wlxoeIa_text","default":"No redness, no peeling, no \"what happened to your face?\" at work."},{"type":"html","id":"gg5z2U-KG0m_text","label":"gg5z2U-KG0m_text","default":"<p>I tried drugstore Retinol once. Big mistake.</p><p><br>Within a week, my face looked like I'd stuck it in a furnace. Red, flaky, peeling skin. My coworkers asked if I had a sunburn. In January. I stopped using it and swore off \"anti-aging\" products entirely.</p><p><br>Then I learned about Retinyl Palmitate—the form of Vitamin A that Omnis uses. It converts to the active compound inside your skin, gradually, instead of attacking the surface all at once.</p><p><br>Same collagen-building benefits. None of the \"molting snake\" phase.</p><p><br>I've been using Omnis for four months now. Not a single day of irritation. Not one flake. I could've been using this the whole time instead of suffering through that Retinol disaster—or worse, giving up on anti-aging altogether because I thought all Vitamin A products were torture devices.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggKhB9VjBVf_text","label":"ggKhB9VjBVf_text","default":"<p>REASON #4</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggYr1SLNWLO_text","label":"ggYr1SLNWLO_text","default":"It doesn't leave my face greasy or shiny—finally."},{"type":"html","id":"ggolz3F6idF_text","label":"ggolz3F6idF_text","default":"<p>This was a dealbreaker for me with other products.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>I work in an office. I meet with clients. I'm on video calls half the day. The last thing I need is to show up looking like I dunked my face in a deep fryer.</p><p><br>I tried beef tallow because everyone on the internet said it was the \"natural\" solution. What they didn't mention was that I'd look like a glazed donut for 8 hours. My pillowcase was ruined. My wife refused to kiss me because I smelled like a steakhouse. And my skin actually broke out worse than before.</p><p><br>Omnis absorbs in about 60 seconds. Completely. No residue. No shine. No grease transfer to my pillow.</p><p><br>I apply it at night and wake up with skin that feels hydrated but looks matte and normal. Not like I'm sweating through a job interview. Not like I forgot to wash my face. Just... normal, healthy skin.</p><p><br>That sounds like a small thing until you've experienced the alternative.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg7UPhcokez_text","label":"gg7UPhcokez_text","default":"<p>REASON #5</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggy1uVJXFHe_text","label":"ggy1uVJXFHe_text","default":"People keep asking if I've \"lost weight\" or \"been on vacation.\""},{"type":"html","id":"gg1-KJcIHG6_text","label":"gg1-KJcIHG6_text","default":"<p>Here's something I didn't expect. After about 6 weeks, people started commenting. But not about my skin directly—they couldn't quite put their finger on what was different.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggFJhsy_CvE_childItem_0","label":"ggFJhsy_CvE_childItem_0","default":"<p>\"Did you lose weight?\"</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggFJhsy_CvE_childItem_1","label":"ggFJhsy_CvE_childItem_1","default":"<p>\"You look rested. Did you just get back from somewhere?\"</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggFJhsy_CvE_childItem_2","label":"ggFJhsy_CvE_childItem_2","default":"<p>\"I don&#039;t know, you just look... healthier.\"</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggrbc_n9wIh_text","label":"ggrbc_n9wIh_text","default":"<p>The funny thing is, I hadn't changed anything else. Same diet. Same exercise (which is to say, not much). Same sleep schedule.</p><p><br>What changed was the structure of my face. When your skin is firmer, your jawline more defined, the bags under your eyes less pronounced—you don't look \"younger\" exactly. You look better. More vital. More present.</p><p><br>People notice. They just don't always know what they're noticing.<br>My barber finally figured it out around month three. \"Your skin looks different,\" he said. \"Tighter. What are you using?\" I told him. He ordered some that night.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggYPrcXD2E5_text","label":"ggYPrcXD2E5_text","default":"<p>REASON #6</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggZD71lV9OF_text","label":"ggZD71lV9OF_text","default":"It has 7,405+ five-star reviews and is the #1 pharmacist recommendation in Italy."},{"type":"html","id":"ggA2y9ipIbW_text","label":"ggA2y9ipIbW_text","default":"<p>I'm skeptical of most things I see advertised online. Especially skincare. Especially stuff that promises to make you \"look 10 years younger.\"</p><p><br>So before I bought Omnis, I did my homework.</p><p><br>What I found: This wasn't some dropshipped mystery cream invented by a marketing agency. It was developed by an Italian pharmaceutical lab and had become the most recommended anti-aging product among Italian pharmacists for men over 40.</p><p><br>72,000+ men had already used it. The reviews weren't generic \"5 stars great product\" fluff—they were detailed stories from guys like me who had tried everything else first and finally found something that worked.</p><p><br>Italians take skincare seriously. Their pharmaceutical regulations are stricter than ours. When Italian pharmacists stake their professional reputation on recommending something, it means the formulation actually meets clinical standards.</p><p><br>That's what convinced me to try it. The results are what convinced me to keep using it.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggISlgpb7s1_text","label":"ggISlgpb7s1_text","default":"<p>REASON #7</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggHZTF0vyR2_text","label":"ggHZTF0vyR2_text","default":"There's literally zero risk. Try it for 60 days—if it doesn't work, you get every penny back."},{"type":"html","id":"gg5BboGBlCA_text","label":"gg5BboGBlCA_text","default":"<p>This is what sealed the deal for me.</p><p><br>Omnis offers a 60-day money-back guarantee. Not 30 days like most companies—60 days. That's enough time to complete the full 8-week transformation timeline and actually see if the collagen rebuilding produces visible results.</p><p><br>If you don't see a difference in your neck, your jawline, your wrinkles—you email their support team and get a full refund. No hoops. No \"restocking fees.\" No interrogation about why you're returning it.</p><p><br>I've been burned by enough skincare products to know that most companies make returns as painful as possible because they know their products don't work.</p><p><br>A 60-day guarantee on an 8-week protocol? That tells me they expect you to see results. They're betting on efficacy, not on you forgetting to return it.</p><p><br>So there's really no excuse not to try it. Worst case: you get your money back and you're exactly where you started. Best case: you finally find the solution that works—like 72,000+ other men already have.</p>"}],
